&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why This Role Exists&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eulerity is an AI-native marketing automation platform — not a legacy tool with AI bolted on. We serve enterprise brands like Mastercard, UPS Store, Uber Eats, and European Wax Center, automating digital advertising across thousands of franchise locations. We&#39;ve crossed $10M ARR, largely bootstrapped, and we&#39;re accelerating.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Android app is a critical surface for how clients interact with the platform — and we&#39;re looking for an intern who doesn&#39;t just write Kotlin, but builds with AI as their primary development tool. At Eulerity, AI-first development isn&#39;t a buzzword — it&#39;s how we actually ship code. Our engineers use Claude Code, agentic coding workflows, and prompt engineering as core parts of their daily process. We expect you to do the same.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll be building features that real users depend on, not a sandbox project that lives in a repo no one checks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;ve shipped an app, already use AI coding tools to move faster than your peers, and know the difference between a good prompt and a great system — read on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Fast Facts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt; $16-18/hour&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; NYC Midtown — 3 days/week in office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule:&lt;/strong&gt; 30 hours/week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Tools:&lt;/strong&gt; Unlimited. Claude Code, Copilot, whatever makes you sharp — we don&#39;t gatekeep tools here.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start Date:&lt;/strong&gt; As soon as possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perks:&lt;/strong&gt; In-office lunches and unlimited snacks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Actually Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn&#39;t a &quot;shadow a senior dev and update button colors&quot; internship. You&#39;ll own real work that ships to real users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take an active role in developing, testing, and maintaining our Android app using AI-first development practices — Agentic coding tools are your daily drivers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement new features end-to-end, from design through deployment, leveraging AI at every stage: architecture decisions, code generation, debugging, testing, and review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write effective prompts and system instructions as a core engineering skill&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with engineers, UX designers, and product managers across all phases of the project lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to building smart, adaptive interfaces that leverage AI to personalize the user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who&#39;s technically sharp, builds with AI by default, and is energized by shipping things that matter — not just completing tickets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Non-Negotiables&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently a student based in the NYC tri-state area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 1 year of Android development experience using Kotlin, Jetpack Compose, and Android Studio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Kotlin (Java experience is a plus) with a solid understanding of the Android SDK and frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You already build with AI — Claude Code, Copilot, or similar agentic coding tools are part of how you work, not something you&#39;ve tried once&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong prompting skills — you understand how to write effective prompts and system instructions to get high-quality output from LLMs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong UI development skills in Jetpack Compose / XML layouts and hands-on experience with Android libraries and APIs (Retrofit, Dagger/Hilt, Room, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Eulerity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eulerity is a rapidly growing technology company revolutionizing marketing automation for small businesses and franchises with our industry-leading proprietary software. Founded by leaders from Google, Facebook, and Yahoo! with more than 20 years of digital advertising, engineering, and marketing experience, we build tools that make enterprise-grade marketing accessible at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Backend Developer with 1–3 years of experience to join our engineering team. You&#39;ll take an active role in building, testing, and maintaining the backend services that power our platform — and you&#39;ll do it with AI as a core part of your workflow, not an afterthought. This is a role for someone who&#39;s genuinely excited about what AI-assisted development makes possible and wants to push that further every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, test, and maintain backend services across Eulerity&#39;s core platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own features end-to-end — from design and implementation through deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI agents and LLM tooling to prototype, iterate, and ship faster&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute product ideas and help shape the engineering roadmap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams on features and releases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with documentation, system support, and knowledge sharing across the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of hands-on backend development experience, with at least 1 year building in Java&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve actually used AI agents (Claude, Copilot, Cursor, or similar) to build, debug, and ship software — not just experimented with them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with LLMs, AI agent frameworks, or AI-assisted development workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable integrating third-party APIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong drive to keep learning — especially when it comes to evolving AI tooling and how it applies to real engineering problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You think creatively about complex problems and enjoy finding elegant solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative, communicative team player with a friendly, low-ego approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based in the NYC tri-state area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Available to work full-time (40 hours/week)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary (commensurate with experience)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full GitHub Copilot access with frontier LLMs and coding agents from Anthropic, Google, and OpenAI — so you&#39;re always working with the best tooling available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship and regular peer review sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unlimited snacks and an in-office lunch credit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid work flexibility with at least three in-office days per week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🩺 Comprehensive benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dental&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🏖️ Unlimited PTO&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🚅 Commuter benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;📈 401(k) with company match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;😎 Summer Fridays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our salary ranges are based on paying competitively for our company&#39;s size and industry, and are one part of the total compensation package that also includes benefits, perks, and other opportunities at Eulerity. The expected tota

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why This Role Exists&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eulerity is an AI-native marketing automation platform — not a legacy tool with AI bolted on. We serve enterprise brands like Mastercard, UPS Store, Uber Eats, and European Wax Center, automating digital advertising across thousands of franchise locations. We&#39;ve crossed $10M ARR, largely bootstrapped, and we&#39;re accelerating.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re not looking for someone who &quot;uses AI tools.&quot; We&#39;re looking for someone who thinks in systems, ships fast, and treats AI as the primary interface between product ideas and execution. You&#39;ll be the closest intellectual partner to our Head of Product — expected to challenge, synthesize, and build, not just take notes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you&#39;ve built projects from scratch, obsessed over product decisions at 2 AM, and know the difference between a great prompt and a great system — read on.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Fast Facts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&amp;nbsp; $100,000 – $130,000&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&amp;nbsp; NYC Midtown — 3–4 days/week in office&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Tools Budget:&amp;nbsp; Unlimited. Use what makes you sharp.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Actually Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-ownership role. You&#39;ll be in the room where product decisions get made, and your voice will matter from day one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner directly with the Head of Product on roadmap definition, feature prioritization, and strategic positioning — acting as a real thought partner, not a note-taker&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools to 10x your throughput: generate user stories, synthesize customer feedback, draft specs, prototype concepts, and accelerate research that would otherwise take days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own a product area end-to-end, including an embedded/SDK surface, from discovery through engineering handoff to post-launch measurement and developer adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run structured experiments: define hypotheses, instrument analytics, read results, and make recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex technical discussions into clear requirements that engineers actually want to build from&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct sharp competitive analysis and market research — and bring the so-what, not just the what&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead sprint ceremonies (standups, planning, retros) with the energy of someone who genuinely cares about shipping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay fluent in what&#39;s happening in AI and marketing tech — and actively bring new ideas into the team&#39;s thinking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a rare combination: technically solid, creatively ambitious, and energized by moving fast in a small team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Non-Negotiables&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are genuinely AI-native — you build with AI, you reason with AI, and all your workflows are built around it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve shipped something real: a side project, a capstone, an app, a tool — something you took from idea to existence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re a fast, clear communicator — written, verbal, and in a whiteboard session&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are based in NYC (or the tri-state area) and can commit to 3–4 days in Midtown&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Product Design, or a related technical field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Big Differentiators&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with LLMs, AI agent frameworks, or AI-assist

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Eulerity is a fast-growing marketing technology company transforming how franchises and small businesses approach digital advertising. Built by former leaders from Google, Facebook, and Yahoo!, our platform combines decades of experience in engineering and marketing to deliver an industry-leading, automated solution. We make it easy to plan, launch, and analyze paid campaigns across Google Search, Meta (Facebook/Instagram), Display, Video, and organic social - all from one intuitive platform. We believe breakthrough results happen when technology, strategy, and creativity come together. By combining automation with human insight, we empower brands to scale smarter, move faster, and grow stronger. Internally, we&#39;re just as committed to growth. We cultivate a culture where ambitious, curious, and driven individuals are empowered to lead, learn, and elevate those around them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing, building, and shipping &lt;strong&gt;developer-facing SDKs&lt;/strong&gt; consumed by other engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Owning the SDK as a product: the public API surface, TypeScript types, semantic versioning, packaging/distribution, backwards compatibility, and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building and maintaining AI-powered automation workflows that connect our product to internal and external systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and testing new features using AI-assisted tooling and autonomous agents, maintaining the codebase, integrating with APIs and data models, and owning the PR lifecycle (writing, reviewing, and incorporating feedback).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating across web, mobile, and backend teams to align on best practices, shared architecture, and product direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with Product and Design to translate designs and prototypes into shipped solutions for our users and the engineers who build on our SDK.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SDK/library builder.&lt;/strong&gt; You design clean, intuitive, hard-to-misuse APIs and think about the developer on the other side of your interface.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI-first engineer.&lt;/strong&gt; You&#39;ve set up custom automation workflows (e.g., wiring Claude or similar LLMs into forms, APIs, or internal tools to replace manual work).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A self-starter who can take ownership of a project and work independently and collaboratively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rigorous about reviewing AI-generated output and taking full ownership of the code you ship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good attention to detail and initiative.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills — including the ability to document an SDK so another engineer can succeed with it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven experience designing and shipping a developer-facing SDK, library, or public API consumed by other engineers&lt;/strong&gt; — including the public API/interface design, semantic versioning, and backwards-compatibility discipline that come with it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong separation-of-concerns judgment&lt;/strong&gt; — able to design framework-agnostic core logic (data, state, domain types) cleanly decoupled from thin, framework-specific bindings, so the same core can support multiple front-end frameworks over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience packaging and distributing libraries: bundling (e.g., tsup, Rollup, Vite), ESM/CJS output, tree-shaking and bundle-size awareness, and npm publishing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2–3 years of professional experience with React &amp;amp; TypeScript&lt;/strong&gt;, including building reusable, composable components and using strong types as a public contract.&lt;/li

&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot; data-sourcepos=&quot;3:1-3:282;41-322&quot;&gt;Eulerity is an AI-native marketing automation platform — not a legacy tool with AI bolted on. We serve enterprise brands including Mastercard, UPS Store, Uber Eats, and European Wax Center, automating digital advertising across thousands of franchise and multi-location businesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot; data-sourcepos=&quot;5:1-5:354;324-677&quot;&gt;We are hiring a Brand Marketing Strategist to own the client relationships that sit at the center of what we do. This is a senior role — we are looking for an experienced operator who has managed enough accounts to know the difference between a client who is satisfied and a client who is actually growing, and who cares about the difference.&lt;/p&gt;
